Title: Object: Ferry boat near Nedssili
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 40 in volume I: a ferry full of passengers at a shore in the centre; on the left, some leaving with their cattle, others seated and resting at the shore, two cows walking towards water, a woman and two children bathing; another boat sailing in the right background; after Mayer; published state. 1801 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.40)
